title: Croajingalong NP - Plants
description: Including Mallacoota. Initial flora list supplied by Parks Victoria.

items.title: Cotula coronopifolia
items.content_text: Taller than usual and with undivided leaves.

items.title: Polyscias sambucifolia subsp. 1
items.content_text: Broadest leaves I've seen on this taxon.

items.title: Schoenus spp.
items.content_text: Flowers on long stalks. Possibly S. brevifolius.

items.title: Comesperma defoliatum
items.content_text: About 50cm tall, leafless, often with just one flower.

items.title: Epacris paludosa
items.content_text: On the 2nd pic the glabrous style can be seen, which distinguishes it from the otherwise almost identical E. lanuginosa.

items.title: Blechnum minus
items.content_text: Young plant - looks like a Pellaea but isn't.

items.title: Sannantha pluriflora
items.content_text: Used to be Baeckea virgata and has recently changed name again from Babingtonia pluriflora (via Babingtonia virgata) to Sannantha pluriflora!

items.title: Goodenia humilis
items.content_text: All plants here had red in upper petals. This occurs sometimes in G. humilis.

items.title: Candalides hyacinthina hyacinthina, Lobelia gibbosa s.s.
Lobelia gibbosa s.s.
items.content_text: First time I've been able to ID this species. Leaves not obviously lobed (so not L. dentata). Under the microscope, seed was 0.2-0.3mm long, reticulate, not 3-angled (so not L. simplicicaulis).

items.title: Apium prostratum subsp. prostratum var. prostratum

items.title: Kennedia rubicunda
items.content_text: Kennedia leaves are bottom left of photo. Climbing on Pittosporum undulatum.
